            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Having seen a potential implementation in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/35253 , I'm having doubts about this because it adds\n\n1. code +\n2. surface area +\n3. jargon\n\n, without eliminating the other mechanisms for configuring... thus it adds a new way to configure, but doesn't allow us to tell users \"just do Z instead\", rather we end up saying \"try X, Y, or now also Z\".\n\nTo review, the motivation is : \n\n> However, some people want to enable these `vim.lsp.<feat>.enable` features per-config\n\nWe need to write down what users currently must do to achieve this. Then see if we can improve the mechanisms for it, perhaps via new stdlib features.\n\n",
